            <title>[LANG-1087] NumberUtils#createNumber() returns positive BigDecimal when negative Float is expected</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LANG-1087</link>
                <project id="12310481" key="LANG">Commons Lang</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;NumberUtils.createNumber(&quot;-0.0&quot;)&lt;/tt&gt; returns &lt;tt&gt;BigDecimal&lt;/tt&gt; with 0 signum.&lt;br/&gt;
Caused by the implementation not checking for sign when extracting mantissa from the input string.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Expected is that negative &lt;tt&gt;Float&lt;/tt&gt; is returned.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
